<font color="#FF0000">THE WAR</font><br>
<tt>Tue Nov 26 16:42:18 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
I think a lot of people don't know what they're talking about when it comes to The Vietnam War.<br>
I don't know what people mean when they say, &quot;..the war was wrong&quot;, or &quot;We shouldn't have gone into the war we couldn't win..&quot;<br>
Was The U.S. involvement in Kuwait wrong?  How about the American presence in Bosnia, in Africa right now? <br>
The U.S. going to Kuwait was right?  Sure.  A giant Iraq invading little Kuwait could not be tolerated.  It was the same thing in Vietnam.  North Vietnam was no any bigger or any more powerful as South Vietnam but it had backing from China and The Soviet Union.  Was it right for the U.S. to stand back and let the little South Vietnam, an ally, to be crushed? Or was it the reason for our going to Kuwait was that there is oil and other resources.  Maybe Vietnam was not very developed and there wasn't much oil discovered at the time.  So why bother going there if we couldn't make mega bucks from the Vietnamese right?  <br>
   How about in Africa?  How much are we going to profit from some of these very poor countries?<br>
It is very easy to say things like &quot;it was a wrong war&quot; or the &quot;war we couldn't win.&quot;  I can understand why some say that The Americans troops shouldn't have gone to Vietnam.  It was that the former president of South Vietnam, Ngo Dinh Diem, did not want the American troops there.  What he and his people need was financial support.  He could not allow someone else to fight for his country.  It was noble the the Americans did but the Vietnamese have pride too.  They wanted Vietnam to belong solely to them.  They did not want to lose their leadership, their ownership of their own country.  But no, The U.S. could not just spend money in that manner.  It was the attitude that &quot;If I am pouring out money, I want to do it my way.&quot;  Take the following example. A person wants to build a custom house the way the size, the everything he likes, none of which is not legal according to the lawhe. He needs some money so he borrows a loan from the bank.  Now should he let the bank build his house in whatever way they want?  I hope not. <br>
It is too sad that The Americans did not understand and agree with former president Ngo Dinh Diem.  That is why one will not find too many sources about him.  The few people who wrote about him did not know and did not understand him that well. The saddest part was that he was murdered by the Americans, the people who thougt were his friends, the people who he had no reason to hate.  Some might say that he was a dictator, that he was a bad man.  Shucks.  How shallow people think.  He did what was best, what was required in those chaotic circumstances of the time.  Imagine what things might have been done to the people or parties of both the North and the South in The U.S. during the American Civil War.<br>
On this ocassion of Thanksgiving, i give many endless thanks to each and all the people who supported  South Viet Nam.  I admire the noble Americans.  I will pray for the souls of those who died for the just cause.  I feel the sorrow for the families broken, physical handicaps and injuries, properties lost, of all who were effected by the war.<br>
I do not represent anyone.  The above is my from my own perspective.  I did not speak for anyone.<br><br>
